INSERT INTO wp_posts VALUES('845', '1', '2012-10-09 17:55:54', '2012-10-09 17:55:54', '{tab=About Crystal Hearing}\r\n<h4>About Crystal Hearing</h4>\r\nLorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit. Donec tortor arcu, pharetra ut vehicula eget, faucibus in urna. Integer tempus fermentum nibh pharetra tempor.\r\n\r\nSed erat risus, auctor sit amet vehicula vitae, tempor et justo. Duis ultrices aliquet tempor. Mauris viverra sem non nunc egestas sit amet vestibulum libero aliquam. Aenean eget sollicitudin erat. Cras elementum lacinia hendrerit.\r\n\r\n{tab=Central Hearing Loss}\r\n<h4>Central Hearing Loss</h4>\r\nWith central hearing loss the issue sits in the central nervous system and not the ear itself. The affected person’s ear might work just fine but they have difficulty understanding what is being said, because central hearing loss affects the ability to filter out competing sounds and noises.\r\n\r\n{tab=Conductive Hearing Loss}\r\n<h4>Conductive Hearing Loss</h4>\r\nWith conductive hearing the inner ear is not effectively receiving sound. There is damage, blockage or some other issue jamming the signal from the outer and/or middle ear.\r\n\r\n{tab=Sensorineural Hearing Loss}\r\n<h4>Sensorineural Hearing Loss</h4>\r\nWhen it comes to sensorineural hearing loss, the damage lies with the inner ear and/or the nerve. Also known as cochlear hearing loss, inner ear hearing loss and nerve deafness. A very large number of hearing issues fall into the “sensorineural” category.\r\n\r\n{tab=Mixed Hearing Loss}\r\n<h4>Mixed Hearing Loss</h4>\r\nMixed hearing loss is when a person has a combination of two or more types of hearing loss. This category is when both sensorineural hearing loss and conductive hearing loss are present.', 'Home Page', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '141-revision-11', '', '', '2012-10-09 17:55:54', '2012-10-09 17:55:54', '', '141', 'http://agdev.ca/crystalhearing/141-revision-11/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
