INSERT INTO wp_posts VALUES('1017', '1', '2012-10-11 17:15:44', '2012-10-11 17:15:44', '<em>Depending on the severity of the hearing loss there are many treatment options available.</em>\r\n\r\nSurgery, listening devices, hearing aids, cochlear implants, signaling and text displays are just a few of the treatments that can help your hearing loss and increase your quality of life.', 'Hearing Loss Treatments', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '375-revision-3', '', '', '2012-10-11 17:15:44', '2012-10-11 17:15:44', '', '375', 'http://agdev.ca/crystalhearing/375-revision-3/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO wp_posts VALUES('1018', '1', '2012-11-01 17:24:59', '2012-11-01 17:24:59', '<em>The myths around hearing loss and hearing aids have been around for years. Since technology and medical advances have improved so much it’s amazing how many myths people still believe. Here’s just a few:</em>\n\n<strong> </strong><strong>Hearing aids are awkward and uncomfortable. </strong>Today’s hearing aids are comfortable, stylish and discreet to the point of being invisible.\n\n<strong> </strong><strong>If I had a hearing problem I\'d know about it. </strong>Quite the opposite is true. Loved ones notice first – a person begins to compensate for the very gradual changes by asking others to repeat words, turn the TV up louder, possibly even reading lips. Allowed to continue, these habits mistakenly make the sufferer believe there is no problem, or that it has gone away.\n\n<strong> </strong><strong>Amplification will make the damage worse. </strong>False. The truth is ignoring your hearing loss can progress it further and cause permanent damage.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2>TRY OUR 5 STEPS TO BETTER HEARING EXERCISE:</h2>\n<h3></h3>\n<h3>1. Admit that I have a permanent hearing loss.</h3>\n<ul>\n	<li>“Honest criticism is hard to take, particularly from a relative, a friend, an acquaintance, or a stranger.” — Franklin P. Jones</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>2. Make a personal choice to achieve better hearing with a good attitude.</h3>\n<ul>\n	<li>“Positive anything is better than negative nothing.” — Elbert Hubbard</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>3. Personal Education: Learn all I can about my hearing loss</h3>\n<ul>\n	<li>“Learning is an active process. We learn by doing. So, if you desire to master the principles you are studying...do something about them. Apply them at every opportunity.” — Dale Carnegie</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>4. Set Realistic Expectations.</h3>\n<ul>\n	<li>“If you still can’t hear your friend speak from across the table at the restaurant on family night, be encouraged — a normal hearing person will have trouble under these circumstances too.” — Thomas Jones</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>5. Practice, Time And Patience: Your Keys to Success.</h3>\n<ul>\n	<li>Some things are not instant, and require time and patience...</li>\n</ul>\n<object width=\"1\" height=\"1\" classid=\"clsid:d27cdb6e-ae6d-11cf-96b8-444553540000\" codebase=\"http://download.macromedia.com/pub/shockwave/cabs/flash/swflash.cab#version=6,0,40,0\"><param name=\"src\" value=\"http://agdev.ca/crystalhearing/wp-content/uploads/2012/11/5-steps-to-better-hearing.pdf\" /><embed width=\"1\" height=\"1\" type=\"application/x-shockwave-flash\" src=\"http://agdev.ca/crystalhearing/wp-content/uploads/2012/11/5-steps-to-better-hearing.pdf\" /><a href=\"http://agdev.ca/crystalhearing/wp-content/uploads/2012/11/5-steps-to-better-hearing.pdf\">5 Steps to Better Hearing</a></object>', 'Hearing Myths', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '447-autosave', '', '', '2012-11-01 17:24:59', '2012-11-01 17:24:59', '', '447', 'http://agdev.ca/crystalhearing/447-autosave/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO wp_posts VALUES('1019', '1', '2012-10-11 17:16:15', '2012-10-11 17:16:15', '<em>The myths around hearing loss and hearing aids have been around for years. Since technology and medical advances have improved so much it’s amazing how many myths people still believe. Here’s just a few:</em>\r\n\r\n<strong> </strong><strong>Hearing aids are awkward and uncomfortable. </strong>Today’s hearing aids are comfortable, stylish and discreet to the point of being invisible.\r\n\r\n<strong> </strong><strong>If I had a hearing problem I\'d know about it. </strong>Quite the opposite is true. Loved ones notice first – a person begins to compensate for the very gradual changes by asking others to repeat words, turn the TV up louder, possibly even reading lips. Allowed to continue, these habits mistakenly make the sufferer believe there is no problem, or that it has gone away.\r\n\r\n<strong> </strong><strong>Amplification will make the damage worse. </strong>False. The truth is ignoring your hearing loss can progress it further and cause permanent damage like dementia.', 'Hearing Myths', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '447-revision-4', '', '', '2012-10-11 17:16:15', '2012-10-11 17:16:15', '', '447', 'http://agdev.ca/crystalhearing/447-revision-4/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
