e totally. They did three things:\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>No more closed caption or volume control high</li>\r\n	<li>Do not withdraw from groups of people</li>\r\n	<li>I feel happy</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nThanks to Jennifer [Maple Ridge] and staff who went the extra mile to help me. I can now live again. And my family and friends are so happy they do not have to keep repeating themselves.\r\n\r\n<em>Can Hear So Many Things Clearly</em>\r\n\r\nI didn\'t realise how impaired my hearing had become until I went for a hearing test at Crystal Hearing Center. The staff there were very courtious and helpful. There was no pressure to buy anything. They were looking out for my best interest. After trying a couple of different models of hearing aids, Andy was able to find the one that was best suited to my needs. I can not say enough about the changes that I have experienced, being able to hear so many things clearly that I now realize that I had been missing. I have recommended my father-in-law and my best friend to Crystal Hearing Center and they are as happy as I am with the result. If you feel that you have a hearing impairment, why wait? Go in and see Andy at the Abbotsford Crystal Hearing Center. You will be glad that you did.\r\n\r\n<strong>-Brent Fairweather, President, Mission Niners Football, Abbotsford, B.C.</strong>\r\n\r\n<em>The Best Hearing Service in Chilliwack</em>\r\n\r\nI didn\'t realize I had a hearing loss. My hearing aids have changed my life completely. I can now hear people clearly and they don\'t have to always repeat themselves. I am very excited and nobody has even noticed them yet.\r\n\r\n<strong>Les Dyble, Abbotsford, B.C.</strong>\r\n\r\n<em>Amazed How Easy it is to Hear</em>\r\n\r\nIt took a long time to talk myself into getting my hearing checked. (Perhaps because I couldn’t hear myself very well.) For the past few years I found watching T.V. or attending meetings becoming less enjoyable. I found it hard to understand what was being said and it gets embarrassing to constantly ask people to repeat themselves.\r\n\r\nAs I walked past Crystal Hearing in the Sevenoaks Mall in Abbotsford, I summoned the courage to go in and make an appointment. Within a couple of weeks I was the proud owner of a pair of Phonak hearing aids. Andy made it easy; making adjustments to ensure I was comfortable with my new hearing aids. I found them easy to get used to. The ability they have to enable me to use my cell phone hands free is an added benefit.\r\n\r\nIt has become as second nature to put in my hearing aids each morning as it is to put on my glasses. I can’t do without either one of them. As a person who has worn glasses for close to sixty years I question why it took so long for me to do something about my hearing.\r\n\r\n<strong>- Pat Parent, Abbotsford, B.C.</strong>\r\n\r\n<em>Hearing Aids Have Changed My Life</em>\r\n\r\nI have had my hearing aids for about 3 months and... I have so much enjoyed listening to the birds sing and being able to participate in the conversation at family and social gatherings. I can honestly say they have changed my life. I feel much more confident and relaxed! For those who would like to enjoy life afresh with the sound of hearing, please don\'t delay. Life is short - why not enjoy the sound of music?\r\n\r\n<strong>- Gladys Merritt</strong>\r\n\r\n<em>Thank You for New Events in My Life</em>\r\n\r\nI have had my hearing aids for only a few days, and these are a few improvements in my life already: on the first day I realized my living room clock had a distinctive tick that I had never heard before; for the first time at my weekly dinner date with my daughter, I never once had to ask [her] what the waiter had said was on special; [I realized] my clothes dryer has a buzzer when the clothes are dry (I was always missing it); I can lower the volume on my TV and radio, and lower it on my phone. Thank you for these new events in my life. I am very grateful for your courtesy in helping me to get used to these wonderful new aids in my life.\r\n\r\n<strong>- Irene Levens</strong>\r\n\r\n<em>Grateful for the kind Way You Helped Me</em>\r\n\r\n[I\'m] sending you this note to let you know how pleased I am with the service you have given me. I don’t mind telling you when I began my search for \"the right hearing aid for me\" I did so with much apprehension.... When I came to [Crystal Vision &amp; Hearing] you spent a lot of time with me, not only doing an extensive and professional hearing test but also you took time to answer all of my questions and you explained in great detail how they work, dispelling my fears about the use of hearing aids.... I love to bake and many times when I put something in the oven and then went about my work the timer would chime but I didn\'t hear it, consequently I had to throw out some good, but badly burned food. Not anymore! Even if I am in a different room I can hear when the warning bell goes off! It is also nice to be able to talk to my friends, even those with very quiet voices, and not have to ask them to repeat what they said. I\'m sure they are glad too! I could go on but I think you get the message that I am very grateful, not just for the hearing aids, but for the kind and willing way you help me with whatever problem I may be having and for your promise of ongoing help whenever I need it. So thank you very much for making this experience a pleasant one. I hope you will be able to help a lot of people who have hearing loss and need someone to guide them through the process of hearing aids.\r\n\r\n<strong>- Bee Pepper</strong>', 'Testimonials', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '884-revision-18', '', '', '2012-11-02 15:53:30', '2012-11-02 15:53:30', '', '884', 'http://agdev.ca/crystalhearing/884-revision-18/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
